On February 5, 2001, the Subcommittee will convene to make its determination

as to the eligibility of the proposed nominees to run in the category for

which they were proposed or otherwise.   Such determination will be

immediately posted.  Should the Subcommittee determine that a proposed

candidate is ineligible to run in the category for which he was recommended,

written notice thereof shall immediately be submitted to that person.  To

assist the Subcommittee, NYMEX members may submit information regarding the

eligibility of a proposed nominee to the Subcommittee.  All such submissions

must be received by 5:00 p.m. on February 9, 2001 at the Office of the

Corporate Secretary.  In addition, a proposed nominee may appeal the

Subcommittee,s categorization.  Such appeal must be made by 5:00 p.m. on

February 9, 2001.  The Subcommittee will consider the appeal and make a final

ruling no later than February 13, 2001.  At that time, the Subcommittee will

assign the proposed nominee!

s !

to the proper categories, regardless of the category for which the proposed

nominee was

originally recommended; however, only persons who were recommended to be

candidates for Chairman are eligible to run for that office.


TO BE OFFICIALLY NOMINATED, EACH PROPOSED NOMINEE WILL BE REQUIRED TO FILE

WITH THE OFFICE OF THE CORPORATE SECRETARY A DECLARATION WHICH STATES THAT

CATEGORY IN WHICH THE PERSON INTENDS TO STAND FOR ELECTION.  FAILURE TO

SUBMIT A DECLARATION TO THE OFFICE OF THE CORPORATE SECRETARY BY 5:00 P.M. ON

TUESDAY, FEBRUARY 20, 2001 WILL RENDER THE PROPOSED NOMINEE INELIGIBLE TO RUN

IN ANY CATEGORY.


Note, only those persons who were proposed by February 2, 2001 will be

permitted to be officially nominated.


Ballots will be mailed no later than February 27, 2001.


The election will be held on Tuesday, March 20, 2001.


Should you have any questions regarding the above, please contact Christopher

Bowen at (212) 299-2200, M. Dawn Lowe at (212) 299-2370 or Donna Talamo at

(212) 299-2372.


